# Users and Groups

## Changing User Name and Password  
```bash
sudo -i  # Must be logged in as different user than one you are changing.
usermod -l new_name old_name # Rename the user
usermod -d /home/new_name -m new_name # Move the home dir to the new username
grep -E "old_namme|new_name" /etc/passwd # Check users and groups
ls -la /home/new_name # Check permissions for new user
reboot
```

## Changing User Password
```bash
sudo passwd [username]
```

## Create User and Add to sudo Group
```bash
sudo adduser NEWUSERNAME
sudo usermod -aG sudo NEWUSERNAME
```